    <h2 class="mt-10 font-sans text-[20px] font-bold tracking-[-0.02em] text-[#292524]">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-[#e5e7eb] bg-white shadow-sm mt-4">
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">How do I ask a customer for a Google review?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">Ask immediately after a positive experience. In person, via text, or email. Use their name, reference the specific service, and include a direct Google review link. Keep it short and low-pressure. "If you have 30 seconds" works better than a long formal request. This tool generates personalized templates for every occasion.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">When is the best time to send a review request?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">For SMS: within 1 hour of service. For email: within 2 hours. For in-person: at checkout. The closer to the experience, the higher the response rate. Follow up 3-5 days later if needed. After resolving a complaint, wait 24-48 hours first.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">Should I ask for reviews via email or text?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">Text messages get 3-5x higher response rates than email. Use both: text for the initial ask (quick, high open rate), email for a follow-up reminder (more space for personalization). In-person asks with QR codes also work very well.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">Is it against Google's rules to ask for reviews?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">No. Google encourages businesses to ask for reviews. What you cannot do is offer incentives (discounts, gifts) for reviews, or selectively ask only satisfied customers (review gating). Asking all customers equally is fine and recommended.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">What tone should I use when asking for a review?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">Match the tone to your relationship with the customer. Friendly works best for casual services (salons, restaurants, fitness). Professional is better for formal services (legal, accounting, medical). Brief is great for SMS where character count matters. After resolving a complaint, be sincere and appreciative without being defensive.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">How do I ask for a review after resolving a complaint?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">Wait 24-48 hours after resolution to give them time to evaluate. Acknowledge the issue briefly, focus on how you fixed it, and ask if they're satisfied. Don't apologize again — just ask if the resolution was good. Only ask if they seem genuinely happy with how you handled it.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">What should I say when asking in person?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">Ask when the customer is happiest — right after a successful outcome, not while they're paying. Use their name, reference the service, and remove all friction: mention the QR code or offer to text the link immediately. "We're so glad you came in today, [name]. If you have a second, we'd really appreciate a quick Google review — I can text you the link right now!"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">How do I get my Google review link?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">Search for your business on Google Maps, click on your listing, and click "Write a review." Copy the URL from your browser. Alternatively, use our Review QR Code Generator tool — it finds your business automatically and gives you both the direct link and a printable QR code.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="border-b border-[#f3f4f6]">
        <button class="tool-faq-btn flex w-full cursor-pointer items-start justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 text-left transition-colors hover:bg-[#fafafa]" aria-expanded="false">
          <span class="font-sans text-[15px] font-semibold text-[#111827]">Should I follow up if a customer doesn't leave a review?</span>
          <svg class="tool-faq-plus mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#9ca3af]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          <svg class="tool-faq-minus hidden mt-0.5 shrink-0 text-[#4f39f6]" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
        </button>
        <div class="tool-faq-answer hidden px-6 pb-5">
          <p class="font-sans text-[14px] leading-[1.7] text-[#4b5563]">Send one polite follow-up 3-5 days after the initial request. After that, let it go. Nobody likes being nagged. The follow-up should be shorter than the first email and acknowledge that they're busy. For complaint resolutions, wait a full week before following up.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
